ActIndian Act
PrecisAcceptance of an Instrument wherein the SEMIAHMOO BAND (a) revokes both a 1943 and a 1947 Surrender affecting Semiahmoo Indian Reserve in British Columbia, and (b) designates, for a term of 99 years, some 14.62 hectares of that same reserve, for the purpose of leasing them to the Se-Mi-Ah-Mu Limited Partnership for the various kinds of ventures specified therein.
